To use:

1. Download the following

	a. maven 3.x
	b. solr (http://lucene.apache.org/solr)
	c. protostuff (http://code.google.com/p/protostuff)
		i. package (.zip)
		ii. java compiler (.jar)
	
2. Install maven

	a. unzip
	b. set $path
	
3. Build protostuff (requires maven, gcc, and an Internet connection)

	a. unzip protostuff-1.0.0.zip
	b. cd into and run the command: mvn install
	
4. Install Solr (use default example)
	a. download solr
	b. ant compile, example
	
4. Create an Eclipse project
	
	a. import project
	b. create user library - protostuff
	
5. Running

	a. start solr (see http://lucene.apache.org/solr/tutorial.html)
		i. cd solr/example
		ii. java -jar start.jar
	b. run: ant full
	c. run: ant test.load
	d. run: ant test.query